reviews.text:
Before I begin, Special Thanks to the workers who assisted me today: Chase, Josh, and Briggs

Wow‚Ä¶ just WOW !! Summit pizza really brought the flavor with this one. I really loved how much Chase brought his special sauce all over my beautiful 16 inch slices. And though Briggs is ONLY a sophomore, he still had a lot to do with the beautiful kaleidoscope of color that just filled me from my stomach to my mouth, all through my throat and everything. I would submit to the workers at Summit Pizza & Co. I WILL be back for extra meaty and delectable Italian meat and maybe some pizza too. From the peacefully free plains of California all the way to the pizza shops in downtown New York, I have never felt such passion (and from the inside of a box ? WOW !!!!). It‚Äôs been quite the panoply of loveliness today with my experience at Summit Pizza, and I WILL be back. It‚Äôs as if I could taste your personal philosophies in nothing more than dough, cheese, and what tasted like BUCKETS of extra special sauce. I love you guys. Keep pleasuring my insides and tastes with such culinary artworks.

Excellent pizza! They most likely have a pizza you love. I just tried the chicken pesto with basalmic glaze. Delish!!! Clean and friendly. Great extras ‚Äúdoodles‚Äù raspberry were my choice but cinnamon are excellent too‚Ä¶ salad, bowls, excellent great food.. sorry I only took a pic of the last slice:) Have gone to the Kamas location for many years- good memories. New owner is awesome and cares about excellence!

The Margarita Pizza was such a disappointment. We couldn‚Äôt get past the first slice and even after taking it back to the counter and politely explaining it was bad, the employee just stared blankly at us, probably not knowing what to do. This place is in dire need of better customer service.

My wife and I decided to give Summit Pizza Co. in Lehi a try, ordering two pizzas and some doodles. Everything seemed fine until we were finishing up at the register. My wife grabbed about six Parmesan cheese packets‚Äînothing excessive for two pizzas‚Äîand the tall, lengthy kid with black hair at the counter immediately decided that was ‚Äúfar too many.‚Äù

Instead of providing good customer service, he condescendingly told us he had worked there for two years and that ‚Äúpeople always grab way too many.‚Äù My wife politely reassured him, saying, ‚ÄúWe will use them all. Trust us.‚Äù But rather than letting paying customers take what they needed, he doubled down, rudely insisting, ‚ÄúNo, you won‚Äôt. Put some back.‚Äù

Excuse me? Since when does a restaurant employee get to micromanage how much Parmesan a customer takes? If the restaurant has a policy, there‚Äôs a professional way to communicate it‚Äînot by embarrassing and arguing with a paying customer. This was not only unnecessary but incredibly rude.

Customer service 101: The customer isn‚Äôt always right, but in situations like this, you absolutely let it go. You don‚Äôt create an awkward, uncomfortable experience over something as insignificant as cheese packets. It‚Äôs a level of pettiness and unprofessionalism I wouldn‚Äôt expect from a place that presumably wants return customers.

The food was fine, but the experience left such a bad taste in our mouths that we won‚Äôt be returning. Plenty of other pizza places in town that actually value their customers‚ÄîSummit Pizza Co. clearly isn‚Äôt one of them.

Worst pizza we‚Äôve ever had, from the crust, cheese and pepperoni. The crust was heavy and dense, tasted like cardboard. The food did not tats fresh at all. A $5 frozen pizza would have been a better option. We also ordered the raspberry and cinnamon doodles. They were overcooked and crunchy. Twelve year olds wouldn‚Äôt even eat them. Don‚Äôt waste your money on this place.

editorial_summary.overview: Casual pizza parlor turning out classic & original pies, plus gluten-free options & patio seating.

customerMoodAnalysis.sentimentSummary: Customers are expressing concerns. The 2.6/5 rating from 5 recent reviews indicates significant opportunities for improvement.

strengthsPerceived: Customers are captivated by the unique and flavorful sauces, particularly Chase's special sauce, which enhances the pizza experience. - social media marketing can showcase this strength
The friendly and passionate staff, including younger team members like Briggs, contribute significantly to the positive dining experience. - review management can highlight this positive aspect

The variety and quality of menu offerings, such as the chicken pesto with balsamic glaze and unique extras like raspberry "doodles," keep customers returning. - Boostly marketing services can amplify this
improvementOpportunities: Poor customer service experiences, such as employees not knowing how to handle complaints and being rude to customers - review management can address this concern
Negative reviews about food quality, such as heavy crust and overcooked items - social media marketing can improve this area
Competition from other pizza places that value customers more - SEO services can solve this visibility issue
